main event: On 7/19/1958, a white pulsating light was observed traveling at great speed for one minute.
interesting points: The object was observed traveling at a great speed in a southeast by south direction.
It was estimated to be at a great height and observed midway between the Square of Pegasus and Altair.
The sighting was reported by three observers and there were official conclusions suggesting it could possibly be a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical object.
No photograph was present in the UFO report.
The report suggests the object was observed traveling on a possible satellite trail.
result: Possibly explained as a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical object according to official data.
location: Undetermined, but estimated at great height
